Subject: [patch-2.3.99-pre3] optimized sysfs(2)
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2000/3/27/39

Hi Linus,
I noticed that file_systems is now protected by a spinlock of its own, in
particular fs_index()/fs_name()/fs_maxindex() are safe and therefore
sys_sysfs() does not need BKL anymore.
Here is the patch:
Thanks,
Tigran.
--- super.c.0	Mon Mar 27 11:41:37 2000
+++ super.c	Mon Mar 27 11:42:10 2000
@@ -192,7 +192,6 @@
 {
 	int retval = -EINVAL;
 
-	lock_kernel();
 	switch (option) {
 		case 1:
 			retval = fs_index((const char *) arg1);
@@ -206,7 +205,6 @@
 			retval = fs_maxindex();
 			break;
 	}
-	unlock_kernel();
 	return retval;
 }
 
-
